[The previous report in this thread recorded a similar upsurge in the
number of mumps cases in Northern Ireland. It is unfortunate that public
suspicion of the triple MMR vaccine remains unallayed, despite the best
efforts of the UK government and medical profession. The 2-dose trivalent
vaccine has been administered to children in Finland over a period of 17
years (1983-1999) and has interrupted circulation of the target viruses. As
a result in 1999 Finland became the first country documented to be free of
indigenous mumps and rubella (measles was eliminated in 1996). - Mod.CP
